ars a sequence of three engravings.

Number one represents a sixteenth-century gentleman in the act of handing a book to a humble fellow who holds a spear and a bay-crowned hat in his left hand. Note the sinistral detail (Why? Ah, 'that is the question,' as Monsieur Homais once remarked, quoting le journal d'hier; a question which is answered in a wooden voice by the Portrait on the title page of the First Folio), Note also the legend: 'Ink, a Drug.' Somebody's idle pencil (Ember highly treasure